  <Docs>
    <remarks>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>The <see cref="T:System.Web.Services.Discovery.DiscoveryRequestHandler" />  class, via its <see cref="M:System.Web.Services.Discovery.DiscoveryRequestHandler.ProcessRequest(System.Web.HttpContext)" /> method, processes an HTTP request for a discovery document. A discovery document is represented by the <see cref="T:System.Web.Services.Discovery.DiscoveryDocument" /> class and is usually serialized as a file using a .disco extension. Web services discovery provides a mechanism for determining the Web services that are available at a given location.</para>
      <para>The <see cref="T:System.Web.Services.Discovery.DiscoveryRequestHandler" />  class normally does not need to be used directly by a developer.</para>
    </remarks>
    <summary>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>An ASP.NET HTTP handler that processes a request for a Web services discovery document.</para>
    </summary>
